definition.value: A glycosyl glycoside consisting of a beta-D-glucopyranose residue and a D-glucitol residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
An (S)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA having (3S)-citryl as the S-acyl group
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-D-mannopyranose and D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A Delta(11)-acyl-CoA having trans-tetradec-11-enoyl as the S-acyl group.

A branched amino nonasaccharide consisting of a D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-[beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and an alpha-L-Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->6)-linkage.
A Delta(11)-acyl-CoA having cis-tetradec-11-enoyl as the S-acyl group.
